		<td><b>sprite zero basic question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />does sprite zero hit when sprites are not visible?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Disch</b> [ Sun Sep 04, 2005 10:30 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />No
<br />
<br />Sprite zero hit happens as the pixels are actually rendered -- if the sprite pixels are not being rendered, the sprite can't be hit.  Both BG and sprites must be enabled -- and for a collision to occur on the left-most 8 pixels of a scanline, the clip option for both BG and sprites must be off.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Sun Sep 04, 2005 11:27 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />And it can't occur on the last pixel of a scanline (x=255).
<br />
<br />But it can occur if the sprite and background are drawn with colors whose palette entries are the same (e.g. black) or if the sprite is drawn behind the background.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


